[{"id":"VR796974","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. Figure 1 shows a rectangular circuit diagram with a resistor of resistance uppercase R and a nonideal battery. The nonideal battery is surrounded by a dashed rectangle and consists of an ideal battery and a resistor of resistance lowercase r. A counterclockwise current I is indicated. Figure 2 is identical to figure 1, except the resistance of the external resistor is 3 uppercase R, and the clockwise current indicated has magnitude I over 2.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR796974.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">When a nonideal battery is connected to a resistor with resistance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, the current in the circuit is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span>. When the same nonideal battery is connected to a resistor with resistance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"3 uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the current in the circuit is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction I over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction I over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span>. What is the internal resistance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase r\"><math alttext=\"lowercase r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> of the battery?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR796974_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction uppercase R over 4\"><math alttext=\"the fraction uppercase R over 4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction uppercase R over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction uppercase R over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"2 uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]